column7: StarLite 150 (GX) drive assembly procedure references an alignment tool “GX-7” which assists in alignment of the X and Y drives. This tool fits into the bearing seat on the fine adjust knob, and keeps the lead screw shaft centered during attachment of the drive. This tool is missing from both QVI and overseas vendor facilities.  New tool T141056 will provide the alignment function of this missing tool.
